  "prompt": "Where can I find a power outlet for my laptop at Melbourne Airport?",
  "response": "Melbourne Airport offers several options for finding power outlets to charge your laptop. Here are some places where you might find them:\n\n1. **Public Seating Areas**: Many seating areas throughout the terminals have power outlets available. Look for seats with integrated power points, especially in newer areas and lounges.\n\n2. **Food Courts and Cafes**: Many cafes and dining areas have outlets you can use. Establishments like McDonald\u2019s, Hudsons Coffee, and other cafes often offer charging points.\n\n3. **Airport Lounges**: If you have access to airline lounges or pay-per-use lounges, you will usually find plenty of power outlets. Lounges like the Qantas Club, Virgin Australia Lounge, and Plaza Premium Lounge are equipped with outlets for charging electronic devices.\n\n4. **Charging Stations**: Some terminals have dedicated charging stations that include multiple power outlets and USB ports. These are typically found in the departure areas.\n\n5. **Gate Areas**: Gates often have power outlets strategically placed for travelers waiting for their flights.\n\nRemember to always keep an eye on your belongings while charging your laptop in public areas. If you're unsure where to find a power outlet, ask airport staff for assistance, and they will likely be able to direct you to the nearest charging spot.",
